node.text:
Which of these colorful birds is your favorite? 😍 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @wanderfervor 

From 1 to 10? 🦜🎨

Names and Photos: 
1. Silver throated Tanager @jeffreypatrickkarnes
2. European Starling @raheel.aazim
3. Mandarin duck @eccentricwildlife
4. Golden-tailed Sapphire @birddetective
5. Strawberry Finch @praharsha_wildlife_stories
6. Periquito-rico @macrotake
7. European Bee-eater @dorugroza
8. Pink Robin @ravi_arora
9. Keel billed Toucan @floriankusterwildlife
10. Oriental Dwarf Kingfisher @rahul_belsare

node.text:
Massive ice sheet breaks away from Glacier in Argentina 🧊 Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @wanderfervor 

Perito Moreno glacier is continuously growing from far behind. The ice break is a spectacular event every year in summertime ☺️

Who would you want to experience this @nature phenomenon with? 🤯

📽 @bruno.guiadeturismo.calafate
📍El Calafate, Argentina

node.text:
Chased by a giraffe! 😳🦒Share your photos with us and we will post them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @wanderfervor 

“This young male giraffe was orphaned at a young age and hand reared until he was able to survive in his own and be released back into to wild. So although this may look like an angry charge, it’s just the giraffe “keeping up with the herd” that he imprinted on as a youngster.

The giraffe chase happened unexpectedly and we did not force this moment. We do not encourage this type of interaction at all and in fact we avoid it at all costs so that the animal remains wild and free from human interaction. This was an unexpected and unavoidable moment.”

📽 @mattyardleyafrica
📍South Africa
